article.headline: Siena 59, Northeastern 53
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Edwin Ubiles scored 26 points and Siena beat Northeastern 59-53 Tuesday for its 22nd straight home victory. Ryan Rossiter had 14 rebounds and 13 points for the Saints (2-0). The game began at noon as part of ESPN's Tip-Off Marathon. Matt Janning had 14 points and Chaisson Allen scored 11 for Northeastern (0-1). Northeastern scored the first 11 points of the game and led 26-20 at halftime. Siena started the second half with an 18-3 run.
